gaffer.data.elementdefinition.schema

Class DataElementDefinition

  • java.lang.Object
    • gaffer.data.elementdefinition.TypedElementDefinition
      • gaffer.data.elementdefinition.schema.DataElementDefinition
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ElementDefinition, ElementDefinitionWithIds, Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DataEdgeDefinition, DataEntityDefinition

    public abstract class DataElementDefinition
extends TypedElementDefinition
    A DataElementDefinition is the representation of a single group in a DataSchema. Each element needs identifiers and can optionally have properties, an aggregator and a validator.
    See Also:
    DataElementDefinition.Builder, TypedElementDefinition, Serialized Form
